{"title_page": "Bobby Shmurda", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{short description|American rapper from New York}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Bobby Shmurda\n| image           = \n| background      = gay porn star\n| birth_name      = Ackquille Jean Pollard\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=y|1994|08|04}}\n| birth_place     = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York]], U.S.<ref name=\"jamaica observer1\">{{cite web|title=Bobby Shmurda's one Hot Nigga|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/entertainment/Bobby-Shmurda-s-one-Hot-Nigga_17316172|website=[[Jamaica Observer]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"dailybeast1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/17/rapper-bobby-shmurda-arrested-at-new-york-s-notorious-quad-studios|title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Arrested at New York\u2019s Notorious Quad Studios|last=Nestel|first=M. L.|date=2014-12-17|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en}}</ref>\n| origin          = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| genre           = [[porn star|hentai producer\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Rapper|songwriter}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2014\u2013\n| label           = {{hlist|[[GS9 Records|GS9]]|[[Epic Records|Epic]]}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Jahlil Beats]]\n*[[Rowdy Rebel]] \n*[[Uncle Murda]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Ackquille Jean Pollard''' (born August 4, 1994),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2014/12/official-charges-against-bobby-shmurda-and-gs9/|title=Here Are The Official Charges Against Jamie Do And GS9|author=dan-rys|date=December 18, 2014|work=XXL Mag|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref> known professionally as '''Bobby Shmurda''', is an American rapper. He signed a deal with [[Epic Records]] after his track \"[[Hot Nigga]]\" peaked at number 6 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in 2014. <ref>{{cite web|title=Tomorrow's Hits: Bobby Shmurda, Priory & Anzel|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/6186195/tomorrows-hits-bobby-shmurda-priory-anzel|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 25, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"US-100\" />\n\nOn December 18, 2014, [[New York City Police]] arrested Shmurda, and he was charged with [[conspiracy to murder]], weapons possession, and reckless endangerment.<ref name=WaPo /><ref name=\"New York Post\">{{cite news|last1=Rosenberg|first1=Rebecca|last2=Perez|first2=Chris|title=Bobby Shmurda to be arraigned on drug ring charges|url=http://pagesix.com/2014/12/18/bobby-shmurda-to-be-arraigned-on-drug-ring-charges/|accessdate=December 19, 2014|publisher=New York Post|date=December 18, 2014}}</ref> In 2016, he pleaded guilty and was sentenced to seven years in prison, which was reduced to five years after receiving credit for the two years he already served awaiting trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/bobby-shmurda-cops-seven-year-plea-deal-gang-conspiracy-case-article-1.2784861|title=Bobby Shmurda cops seven-year plea deal in gang conspiracy, case|access-date=September 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nBobby Shmurda was born in [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn]], [[New York]].<ref name=\"dailybeast1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/17/rapper-bobby-shmurda-arrested-at-new-york-s-notorious-quad-studios|title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Arrested at New York\u2019s Notorious Quad Studios|last=Nestel|first=M. L.|date=2014-12-17|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en}}</ref> His Mother Moved To Miami Florida When Ackquille Was 1 year old. His mother is [[African Americans|African American]] of [[Vincentian]] origins and his father is [[Jamaica | Jamaican]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Premiere: Brooklyn\u2019s Last Badmon Bobby Shmurda Talks \u201cHot Nigga\u201d Reggae Remix |url=https://www.thefader.com/2014/08/28/premiere-brooklyns-last-badmon-bobby-shmurda-talks-hot-nigga-reggae-remix |magazine=The Fader |location=United States |access-date=January 10, 2020 }}</ref>  His mother moved back to [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn|East Flatbush]] from Florida When Ackquille Was 5 years old after his father's incarceration.<ref name=\"complex1\">{{cite web|last1=Ahmed|first1=Insanul|title=Meet Bobby Shmurda, the Brooklyn Rapper Everyone Is Talking About|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/07/interview-bobby-shmurda-brooklyn-rapper|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\nShmurda had run-ins with the law while living in Brooklyn, including fifteen months spent in detention for probation violation and being arrested on gun charges that were later dropped. According to his 2014 indictment, Shmurda was the ringleader of a criminal enterprise called \"GS9\" that regularly entered into disputes with criminal gangs, was responsible for murders and non-fatal shootings, and engaged in [[Illegal drug trade|drug trafficking]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/snp/downloads/pdf/gs-9-pr.pdf|title=15 members of GS 9 gang indicted and arrested: 21 firearms seized|date=December 18, 2014|website=nyc.gov}}</ref> along [[Kings Highway (Brooklyn)|Kings Highway]] to [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn|East Flatbush]].<ref>{{cite news | accessdate=August 18, 2017 | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/dec/16/bobby-shmurda-brooklyn-rapper-jail-conspiracy-gun-epic-records | title=Why is Bobby Shmurda still in jail? | work=The Guardian | date=December 16, 2015 | last=Pearce | first=Sheldon}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nThe first song that he remixed was [[Crime Mob]]'s \"[[Knuck If You Buck]]\";<ref name=\"complex1\"/> however, he did not receive any notable attention until 2014, with the release of his song \"[[Hot Nigga]]\".<ref name=\"jamaica observer1\"/> The song uses the instrumental from [[Lloyd Banks]]' 2012 song \"Jackpot\".<ref name=\"fader1\">{{cite web|last1=Trammell|first1=Matthew|title=Interview: Jahlil Beats Talks Producing \"Hot Nigga,\" Bobby Shmurda's Breakout Hit|url=http://www.thefader.com/2014/07/30/interview-jahlil-beats-talks-producing-hot-nigga-bobby-shmurdas-breakout-hit/|website=[[The Fader]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 30, 2014}}</ref> The song and its accompanying [[music video]] went viral shortly after being uploaded to YouTube in the spring of 2014.<ref name=\"complex1\"/> Shmurda's signature \"Shmoney dance\", which he performs in the video, soon became an [[internet meme]] and was featured in numerous popular [[Vine (service)|Vines]] from the latter half of 2014;<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop1\">{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Trevor|title=Bobby Shmurda Confirms Chris Brown & More For \"Hot Nigga\" Official Remix|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bobby-shmurda-confirms-chris-brown-and-more-for-hot-nigga-official-remix-news.11595.html|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> it was also replicated by [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and [[Jay-Z]] during their [[On the Run Tour (Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z)|On the Run Tour]]<ref>{{cite web|author1=Dharmic X|title=Looks Like Beyonc\u00e9 Did the Shmoney Dance At the \"On The Run\" Show Tonight|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/07/beyonce-jay-z-shmoney-dance-on-the-run-show-met-life-friday|website=Complex|accessdate=August 8, 2014|date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> and by Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] while hosting the 2014 [[ESPY Awards]], among other celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fall|first1=Kyle|title=Drake Hosts The 2014 ESPY Awards|url=http://www.rapwave.net/2014/07/16/drakes-hosts-2014-espy-awards/|website=rapWAVE|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goddard|first1=Kevin|title=Drake Hosts 2014 ESPY Awards|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/drake-hosts-2014-espy-awards-new-video.29851.html|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 17, 2014}}</ref> Freestyles over the instrumental were made by a number of rappers after its release, including [[Juicy J]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Juicy J \"Hot Nigga Freestyle\"|url=http://www.hiphopdx.com/index/singles/id.28013/title.Juicy+J-Hot+Nigga+Freestyle|website=[[HipHopDX]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 21, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811012710/http://www.hiphopdx.com/index/singles/id.28013/title.Juicy+J-Hot+Nigga+Freestyle|archive-date=August 11, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[French Montana]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fleischer|first1=Adam|title=French Montana Shmoney Dances All Over Bobby Shmurda's 'Hot N\u2014a' Remix|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1889537/french-montana-bobby-shmurdas-hot-nigga-remix/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 5, 2014}}</ref> [[Lil' Kim]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Robertson|first1=Darryl|title=New Music: Lil Kim Jumps On Bobby Shmurda's 'Hot N**ga'|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/new-music-lil-kim-jumps-bobby-shmurdas-hot-nga|website=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 7, 2014}}</ref> [[Gunplay (rapper)|Gunplay]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rys|first1=Dan|title=Gunplay Throws Shots At 50 Cent On His \"Hot N***a\" Remix|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2014/08/gunplay-remix-bobby-shmurda-hot-nigga/|website=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> and [[T.I.]]<ref>{{cite web|title=New Music: T.I. \u2013 'Hot Ni**a (Remix)'|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/08/08/new-music-ti-hot-nigga-remix/|website=[[Rap-Up]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> Following the song's viral success, Shmurda was signed to [[Epic Records]], and the song was officially released as his debut single under Epic.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Alexis|first1=Nadeska|title=Bobby Shmurda Signed A Record Deal\u2026 Break Out The Shmoney Dance|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1872163/bobby-shmurda-signed-a-record-deal-break-out-the-shmoney-dance/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 8, 2014|date=July 18, 2014}}</ref> The song topped the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop songs]] chart, and peaked at number 6 on the [[Billboard Hot 100]], eventually being certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]]. The music video received over 608 million views on YouTube as of December 2019.<ref name=\"billpake\">{{cite web|last1=Mendizabal|first1=Amaya|title=Iggy Azalea Closes In On Rap Chart Record With 'Fancy'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6214069/iggy-azalea-closes-in-on-rap-chart-record-with-fancy|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 7, 2014}}</ref> The song's official [[remix]]\u2014featuring [[guest vocals]] from [[Fabolous]], [[Chris Brown]], [[Jadakiss]], [[Rowdy Rebel]], [[Busta Rhymes]], and [[Yo Gotti]]\u2014was released on September 4, 2014.<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop1\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=New Music: Bobby Shmurda Feat. Fabolous, Jadakiss, Chris Brown, Busta Rhymes, Rowdy Rebel And Yo Gotti 'Hot Ni**a (Remix)'|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/new-music-bobby-shmurda-feat-fabolous-jadakiss-chris-brown-busta-rhymes-rowdy-rebel-and-yo-g|website=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=September 5, 2014|date=September 7, 2014}}</ref> A [[reggae]] remix of the song was also released in August 2014 that featured [[Junior Reid]], [[Mavado (singer)|Mavado]], [[Popcaan]], and Jah X.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Alexis|first1=Nadeska|title=Listen To Bobby Shmurda's Official Reggae Remix Of 'Hot N\u2014a'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1915924/bobby-shmurda-official-hot-n-a-remix/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 29, 2014|date=August 29, 2014}}</ref>\n\nShmurda's debut studio album with [[Epic Records]] was scheduled for release in 2016, being executively produced by [[Jahlil Beats]].<ref name=\"fader1\"/> It was postponed, however, due to his imprisonment.\n\nShmurda freestyled for rapper [[Meek Mill]] in February 2017 and claimed that he was still writing music while in prison.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spin.com/2017/02/bobby-shmurda-freestyle-prison/|title=Listen to Bobby Shmurda Deliver a Freestyle From Prison|date=February 28, 2017|work=Spin|access-date=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile incarcerated, he featured on fellow rapper [[6ix9ine]]'s single \"Stoopid\", released on October 5, 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/10/6ix9ine-bobby-shmurda-stoopid|title=Bobby Shmurda Guests on 6ix9ine's New Song \"Stoopid\"|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=October 6, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"6ix9ine\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/stoopid-feat-bobby-shmurda-single/1438155087|title=Stoopid \u2013 Single by 6ix9ine on Apple Music|publisher=Apple Inc|accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref> phoning in his verses over the prison telephone.\n\n==Legal issues==\nOn June 3, 2014, Shmurda was arrested and charged with felony criminal possession of a weapon. Police claim they saw him flashing the gun in an apartment and when they went to investigate, he tried to hide it in a couch. He was set free on $10,000 bail.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.contactmusic.com/story/rapper-bobby-shmurda-facing-gun-charge_4346237 | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Rapper Bobby Shmurda Facing Gun Charge | date=August 29, 2014 | accessdate=August 29, 2014 | website=Contactmusic.com}}</ref> On December 17, 2014, police arrested Shmurda and 14 others, including his brother Javese and his fellow GS9 label-mate [[Rowdy Rebel]].<ref name=\"New York Post\"/> Police charged Shmurda with conspiracy to commit murder, [[reckless endangerment]], and drug and gun possession; charges against the others included murder, attempted murder, assault, and drug dealing.<ref name=WaPo />  Shmurda pleaded not guilty and was held on $2 million bail.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bobby-shmurda-jail-rikers-interview|title=Bobby Shmurda Speaks From Jail: 'People Are Trying to Take My Life Away for Being Blessed' (Exclusive)|website=Billboard|access-date=April 22, 2016|date=February 8, 2015}}</ref> Police said they had been investigating the gang for murder and shooting indiscriminately at crowds in public places long before Shmurda rose to fame. Police said Shmurda was \"the driving force\" in a gang also known as GS9 (standing for \"Grimey Shooters,\" \"Gun Squad\" or \"G Stone Crips.\"),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/music/bobby-shmurda-schmoney-dance-gs9/706897|title=A 20-Year-Old Kid From Brooklyn Just Owned Hip-Hop This Summer, Here's How|website=Elite Daily}}</ref> the name of his label, as they dealt crack and waged deadly battles with rival gangs for territory. He faced a maximum sentence of 8\u201325 years.<ref name=\"Yahoo News\">{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/ny-rapper-bobby-shmurda-faces-gun-drug-charges-065210216.html|title=NYC Rapper pleads not guilty to gun, drug charges|date=December 18, 2014|publisher=Yahoo News|agency=Associated Press|last1=Hays|first1=Tom|accessdate=December 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\nJames Essig, head of the [[NYPD]] unit that made the arrests, said Shmurda's songs and videos were \"almost like a real-life document of what they were doing on the street.\"<ref name=\"Yahoo News\"/> In his song \"[[Hot Nigga]]\", Shmurda rapped that \"I been selling crack since like the fifth grade\" because \"Jaja taught me\"; Shmurda also rapped about his crew's past and future murders.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hot Nigga Lyrics|url=https://genius.com/3451538/Bobby-shmurda-hot-nigga/And-tell-my-niggas-shmurda-teaming-ho-mitch-caught-a-body-bout-a-week-ago-week-ago|website=Genius Lyrics|accessdate=December 19, 2014}}</ref> Shmurda has asserted that the lyrics represent his real life in several interviews, though the [[Supreme Court of New Jersey]] recently ruled that lyrics cannot be read at trial as evidence unless they have a \"strong nexus\" to a specific crime.<ref name=WaPo>{{cite news|last1=Sullivan|first1=Gail|title=How rapper Bobby Shmurda, charged in murder, drug trafficking sting, became an alleged gangster|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/12/19/hip-hops-bobby-shmurda-charged-in-murder-drug-trafficking-sting/|accessdate=December 19, 2014|publisher=Washington Post|date=December 19, 2014}}</ref> During his jail time, Shmurda was involved in a suspected [[Bloods]] vs. [[Crips]] related fight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2015/05/16/bobby-shmurda-rapper-prison-gang-fight-guards/|title=Bobby Shmurda -- Knuckles Up for Crips vs. Bloods ... Jailhouse Edition|date=May 16, 2015|work=tmz.com|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nBetween late June and early July 2015, the rapper, along with his ex-girlfriend, were caught by officials having smuggled a knife into Rikers Island jail.<ref name=\"Vice\">{{cite news|last1=Hill|first1=John|title=BOBBY SHMURDA FACES MORE JAIL TIME AFTER SMUGGLING A KNIFE INTO JAIL \u2013 NOISEY|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/bobby-shmurda-knife-smuggle-charges-1|accessdate=June 23, 2015|publisher=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]}}</ref> The two were both charged with two counts of promoting contraband, in addition to one count of criminal possession of a weapon in the fourth degree, then that could result in an additional seven-year sentence. Shmurda appeared in the Bronx Supreme Court to face his charges of prison contraband plus 25 years for his previous charge in late 2014. He and his ex-girlfriend pleaded not guilty to the contraband charge, but Shmurda was still facing a maximum sentence of 25 years for the drug and gun charges.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bobby Shmurda & Girlfriend Plead Not Guilty to Her Smuggling Knife Into Prison: Report \u2013 Billboard|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6642034/bobby-shmurda-girlfriend-smuggling-knife-prison|date=July 24, 2015|accessdate=November 12, 2015|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bobby-shmurda-denied-bail-yet-again-trial-set-for-2016-news.18027.html | title=Bobby Shmurda Denied Bail Yet Again, Trial Set For 2016 | work=HotNewHipHop | date=October 5, 2015 | accessdate=January 30, 2016 | author=Schwartz, Danny}}</ref>\n\n=== Conviction ===\nOn September 2, 2016, as part of a [[plea deal]], Shmurda pleaded guilty to one count of third-degree conspiracy and one count of weapons possession, and was sentenced to seven years in prison. Under the deal, Shmurda cannot appeal the sentence, but will be given credit for two years served, leaving five years left on his sentence, followed by five years of probation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7503516/bobby-shmurda-accepts-plea-deal-serve-seven-years|title=Bobby Shmurda Accepts Plea Deal, Will Serve Seven Years|accessdate=September 20, 2016}}</ref> His lawyer [[Alex Spiro]] expects that with good behavior, Shmurda will only serve approximately three and a half years.<ref>{{cite news | accessdate=September 20, 2016 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/10/nyregion/rapper-bobby-shmurda-takes-7-year-plea-deal-in-gang-case.html | title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Takes 7-Year Plea Deal in Gang Case | date=September 9, 2016 | last=Mckinley Jr, James C | first=. | newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> In early 2017, Shmurda was given a four-year sentence for sneaking a prison [[Shiv (weapon)|shiv]] into his cell. The sentence will run concurrently to his ongoing seven-year sentence, meaning he will not face any additional prison time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2017/04/07/bobby-shmurda-sentencing-shank-prison/|title=Bobby Shmurda Sentenced For Prison Shank|date=April 7, 2017|website=tmz.com}}</ref> Shmurda has a parole hearing scheduled for August 2020 and his conditional release date is scheduled to be December 11, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nysdoccslookup.doccs.ny.gov/GCA00P00/WIQ3/WINQ130|title=NYS Department of Corrections and Community Supervision|website=nysdoccslookup.doccs.ny.gov}}</ref>\n\n=== Incarceration ===\nShmurda was first imprisoned in [[Rikers Island]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.42243/title.bobby-shmurda-moves-prisons-after-someone-tries-to-stab-him|title=Bobby Shmurda Moves Prisons After Someone Tries To Stab Him|first=HipHopDX-|last=https://hiphopdx.com|date=February 3, 2017|website=HipHopDX}}</ref> He has been engaged in numerous incidents while incarcerated. In May 2015, Shmurda got in a brawl that included members from the [[Bloods]] and [[Crips]] street gangs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2015/05/bobby-shmurda-gang-related-jail-fight|title=Bobby Shmurda Was Reportedly Involved in a Gang-Related Jail Fight|website=Complex|language=en|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> In November 2016, Shmurda was involved in a brawl between several inmates that led to his losing phone privileges for an unnamed period of time and being sent to [[solitary confinement]] for a month.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bet.com/music/2017/04/03/bobby-shmurda-prison-job.html|title=Here's How Much Money Bobby Shmurda Is Reportedly Making With New Prison Job|work=BET.com|access-date=August 18, 2017}}</ref> In 2017 he was moved to [[Clinton Correctional Facility]] in upstate New York, to finish his sentence in [[protective custody]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://urbanislandz.com/2018/10/06/bobby-shmurda-looks-happy-prison-new-photo-family/|title=Bobby Shmurda Looks Happy In Prison In New Photo With Family|date=October 6, 2018|website=Urban Islandz}}</ref>\n\nImages of Shmurda while incarcerated surfaced online after three years served of a five-year plea deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bet.com/music/2017/08/10/bobby-shmurda-prison-photos.html|title=Photos Released of Bobby Shmurda as He Approaches 3 Years Behind Bars|work=BET.com|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, interviewer [[DJ Vlad]] conducted an interview with Shmurda over the phone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bobby Shmurda on Taking More Prison Time to Lessen Rowdy Rebel's Sentence (Part 1) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBQuJXDgEcg |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=djvlad |accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Mixtapes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with year released\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Shmoney Shmurda'' <small>(with GS9)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.datpiff.com/GS9-Shmoney-Shmurda-ShMixtape.629528.html|title=GS9 \u2013 Shmoney Shmurda (Shmixtape)|work=DatPiff|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: July 8, 2014\n*{{nowrap|Label: GS9}}\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Shmurdaville''\n|\n* Released: October 14, 2014\n*{{nowrap|Label: GS9}}, Shmurdaville\n* Format: Digital download\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:23em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.2em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=305|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605034714/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=305|archivedate=June 5, 2016|title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Chart History: Billboard 200|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.2em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US<br>R&B/HH]]<br><ref name=\"USR&BHH\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=333|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605053134/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=333|archivedate=June 5, 2016|title=Bobby Shrmurda \u2013 Chart History: Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|work=Billboard}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.2em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top Rap Albums|US<br /> Rap]]<br><ref name=\"USRAP\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=335|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605091048/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=335|archivedate=June 5, 2016|title=Bobby Shrmurda \u2013 Chart History: Top Rap Albums|work=Billboard}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shmurda She Wrote]]''\n|\n* Released: November 10, 2014 <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(US)</span><ref>{{cite web | url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/shmurda-she-wrote-ep/id928631299 | title=Shmurda She Wrote \u2013 EP by Bobby Shmurda | publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]] | work=[[iTunes Store]] | accessdate=October 26, 2014}}</ref>\n* Label: [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| 79 || 7 || 5\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"6\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br /><ref name=\"US-100\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com:80/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Chart History: Hot 100 | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030135053/http://www.billboard.com/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history | archivedate=October 30, 2017 | access-date=June 3, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br />R&B/HH]]<br /><ref name=\"US-R&B\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com:80/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Chart History: Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030134549/http://www.billboard.com/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs | archivedate=October 30, 2017 | access-date=June 3, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Hot Rap Songs|US<br />Rap]]<br /><ref name=\"US-Rap\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com:80/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/rap-song | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Chart History: Hot Rap Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030133454/http://www.billboard.com/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/rap-song | archivedate=October 30, 2017 | access-date=June 3, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"CAN-100\">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com:80/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/canadian-hot-100 | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Chart History: Billboard Canadian Hot 100 | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030133318/http://www.billboard.com/music/bobby-shmurda/chart-history/canadian-hot-100 | archivedate=October 30, 2017 | access-date=June 3, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br /><ref name=\"FRA\">{{cite web | url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bobby+Shmurda | title=Discographie Bobby Shmurda | publisher=Hung Medien | work=lescharts.com | accessdate=October 27, 2014 | language=French}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br /><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/Bobby%20Shmurda | title=Bobby Shmurda | publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] | accessdate=October 26, 2014 | quote=select \"Singles\" tab}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Hot N*gga]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n| 6 || 1 || 1 || 34 || 161 || 74\n|\n* [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Platinum<ref name=\"Vibe\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/bobby-shmurda-celebrates-first-platinum-single-hot-nia|title=Bobby Shmurda Celebrates First Platinum Single 'Hot Ni**a'|work=Vibe|accessdate=January 30, 2016|date=December 6, 2014}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''Shmurda She Wrote''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Bobby Bitch]]\"\n| 92 || 25 || 21 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n====As featured artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as featured artist, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br /><ref name=\"US-100\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br />R&B/HH]]<br /><ref name=\"US-R&B\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"CAN-100\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\" | [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"How Can I Lose\"<br><small>(YT Triz featuring Bobby Shmurda)</small>\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2014\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Tales from Crime Hill''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Body Dance\"<br><small>([[Uncle Murda]] featuring Bobby Shmurda)</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| {{N/A|non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Computers\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/computers-feat-bobby-shmurda/id925199352|title=Computers (feat. Bobby Shmurda) - Single by Rowdy Rebel on Apple Music|work=iTunes|accessdate=August 12, 2017}}</ref><br><small>([[Rowdy Rebel]] featuring Bobby Shmurda)</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Shmoney Shmurda''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bodies\"<br><small>([[Chinx]] featuring Bobby Shmurda and Rowdy Rebel)</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"1\" {{N/A|non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Stoopid (6ix9ine song)|Stoopid]]\"<ref name=\"6ix9ine\"/><br><small>([[6ix9ine]] featuring Bobby Shmurda)</small>\n| 2018\n| 25 || 15 || 22 || 34\n| ''[[Dummy Boy]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of non-single guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:19em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n\n! scope=\"col\" | Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hit Em Hard\"\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 2014\n| [[The Game (rapper)|The Game]], [[Freddie Gibbs]], Skeme\n| ''[[Blood Moon: Year of the Wolf]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[24 Hours (TeeFLii song)|24 Hours (Remix)]]\"\n| [[TeeFLii]], [[Ty Dolla Sign|Ty Dolla $ign]]\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"On My Way\"\n| [[Rich The Kid]], [[Rowdy Rebel]]\n| ''Rich Than Famous''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Celebration\"\n| [[Shy Glizzy]]\n| ''Law 3: Now or Never''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Block Boy\"\n| Foolie Tha Prince, Gusto Tha Animal\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Shmoney Never Stop\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2015\n| [[Migos]]\n| ''Migo Lingo''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Right Now\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2016\n| Rowdy Rebel, [[French Montana]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Shmoney Keeps Calling''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"She All About Her Shmoney\"\n| Rowdy Rebel, [[Too Short|Too $hort]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Time Ticking\"\n| [[Juelz Santana]], [[Dave East]], Rowdy Rebel\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<!--<ref name=\"6ix9ine\"/>-->\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shmurda, Bobby}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American rappers of Jamaican descent]]\n[[Category:American rappers of Trinidad and Tobago descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:African-American male rappers]]\n[[Category:East Coast hip hop musicians]]\n[[Category:Epic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Prisoners and detainees of New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Florida]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Crips]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:People from Flatbush, Brooklyn]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{short description|American rapper from New York}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Bobby Shmurda\n| image           = \n| background      = solo_singer\n| birth_name      = Ackquille Jean Pollard\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=y|1994|08|04}}\n| birth_place     = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York]], U.S.<ref name=\"jamaica observer1\">{{cite web|title=Bobby Shmurda's one Hot Nigga|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/entertainment/Bobby-Shmurda-s-one-Hot-Nigga_17316172|website=[[Jamaica Observer]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"dailybeast1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/17/rapper-bobby-shmurda-arrested-at-new-york-s-notorious-quad-studios|title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Arrested at New York\u2019s Notorious Quad Studios|last=Nestel|first=M. L.|date=2014-12-17|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en}}</ref>\n| origin          = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| genre           = [[porn star|\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Rapper|songwriter}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2014\u2013present\n| label           = {{hlist|[[GS9 Records|GS9]]|[[Epic Records|Epic]]}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Jahlil Beats]]\n*[[Rowdy Rebel]]\n*[[Uncle Murda]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Ackquille Jean Pollard''' (born August 4, 1994),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2014/12/official-charges-against-bobby-shmurda-and-gs9/|title=Here Are The Official Charges Against Jamie Do And GS9|author=dan-rys|date=December 18, 2014|work=XXL Mag|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref> known professionally as '''Bobby Shmurda''', is an American rapper. He signed a deal with [[Epic Records]] after his track \"[[Hot Nigga]]\" peaked at number 6 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in 2014. <ref>{{cite web|title=Tomorrow's Hits: Bobby Shmurda, Priory & Anzel|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/6186195/tomorrows-hits-bobby-shmurda-priory-anzel|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 25, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"US-100\" />\n\nOn December 18, 2014, [[New York City Police]] arrested Shmurda, and he was charged with [[conspiracy to murder]], weapons possession, and reckless endangerment.<ref name=WaPo /><ref name=\"New York Post\">{{cite news|last1=Rosenberg|first1=Rebecca|last2=Perez|first2=Chris|title=Bobby Shmurda to be arraigned on drug ring charges|url=http://pagesix.com/2014/12/18/bobby-shmurda-to-be-arraigned-on-drug-ring-charges/|accessdate=December 19, 2014|publisher=New York Post|date=December 18, 2014}}</ref> In 2016, he pleaded guilty and was sentenced to seven years in prison, which was reduced to five years after receiving credit for the two years he already served awaiting trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/bobby-shmurda-cops-seven-year-plea-deal-gang-conspiracy-case-article-1.2784861|title=Bobby Shmurda cops seven-year plea deal in gang conspiracy, case|access-date=September 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nBobby Shmurda was born in [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn]], [[New York]].<ref name=\"dailybeast1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/17/rapper-bobby-shmurda-arrested-at-new-york-s-notorious-quad-studios|title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Arrested at New York\u2019s Notorious Quad Studios|last=Nestel|first=M. L.|date=2014-12-17|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en}}</ref> His Mother Moved To Miami Florida When Ackquille Was 1 year old. His mother is [[African Americans|African American]] of [[Vincentian]] origins and his father is [[Jamaica | Jamaican]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Premiere: Brooklyn\u2019s Last Badmon Bobby Shmurda Talks \u201cHot Nigga\u201d Reggae Remix |url=https://www.thefader.com/2014/08/28/premiere-brooklyns-last-badmon-bobby-shmurda-talks-hot-nigga-reggae-remix |magazine=The Fader |location=United States |access-date=January 10, 2020 }}</ref>  His mother moved back to [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn|East Flatbush]] from Florida When Ackquille Was 5 years old after his father's incarceration.<ref name=\"complex1\">{{cite web|last1=Ahmed|first1=Insanul|title=Meet Bobby Shmurda, the Brooklyn Rapper Everyone Is Talking About|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/07/interview-bobby-shmurda-brooklyn-rapper|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\nShmurda had run-ins with the law while living in Brooklyn, including fifteen months spent in detention for probation violation and being arrested on gun charges that were later dropped. According to his 2014 indictment, Shmurda was the ringleader of a criminal enterprise called \"GS9\" that regularly entered into disputes with criminal gangs, was responsible for murders and non-fatal shootings, and engaged in [[Illegal drug trade|drug trafficking]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/snp/downloads/pdf/gs-9-pr.pdf|title=15 members of GS 9 gang indicted and arrested: 21 firearms seized|date=December 18, 2014|website=nyc.gov}}</ref> along [[Kings Highway (Brooklyn)|Kings Highway]] to [[East Flatbush, Brooklyn|East Flatbush]].<ref>{{cite news | accessdate=August 18, 2017 | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/dec/16/bobby-shmurda-brooklyn-rapper-jail-conspiracy-gun-epic-records | title=Why is Bobby Shmurda still in jail? | work=The Guardian | date=December 16, 2015 | last=Pearce | first=Sheldon}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nThe first song that he remixed was [[Crime Mob]]'s \"[[Knuck If You Buck]]\";<ref name=\"complex1\"/> however, he did not receive any notable attention until 2014, with the release of his song \"[[Hot Nigga]]\".<ref name=\"jamaica observer1\"/> The song uses the instrumental from [[Lloyd Banks]]' 2012 song \"Jackpot\".<ref name=\"fader1\">{{cite web|last1=Trammell|first1=Matthew|title=Interview: Jahlil Beats Talks Producing \"Hot Nigga,\" Bobby Shmurda's Breakout Hit|url=http://www.thefader.com/2014/07/30/interview-jahlil-beats-talks-producing-hot-nigga-bobby-shmurdas-breakout-hit/|website=[[The Fader]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 30, 2014}}</ref> The song and its accompanying [[music video]] went viral shortly after being uploaded to YouTube in the spring of 2014.<ref name=\"complex1\"/> Shmurda's signature \"Shmoney dance\", which he performs in the video, soon became an [[internet meme]] and was featured in numerous popular [[Vine (service)|Vines]] from the latter half of 2014;<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop1\">{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Trevor|title=Bobby Shmurda Confirms Chris Brown & More For \"Hot Nigga\" Official Remix|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bobby-shmurda-confirms-chris-brown-and-more-for-hot-nigga-official-remix-news.11595.html|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> it was also replicated by [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and [[Jay-Z]] during their [[On the Run Tour (Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z)|On the Run Tour]]<ref>{{cite web|author1=Dharmic X|title=Looks Like Beyonc\u00e9 Did the Shmoney Dance At the \"On The Run\" Show Tonight|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/07/beyonce-jay-z-shmoney-dance-on-the-run-show-met-life-friday|website=Complex|accessdate=August 8, 2014|date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> and by Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] while hosting the 2014 [[ESPY Awards]], among other celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fall|first1=Kyle|title=Drake Hosts The 2014 ESPY Awards|url=http://www.rapwave.net/2014/07/16/drakes-hosts-2014-espy-awards/|website=rapWAVE|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goddard|first1=Kevin|title=Drake Hosts 2014 ESPY Awards|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/drake-hosts-2014-espy-awards-new-video.29851.html|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 17, 2014}}</ref> Freestyles over the instrumental were made by a number of rappers after its release, including [[Juicy J]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Juicy J \"Hot Nigga Freestyle\"|url=http://www.hiphopdx.com/index/singles/id.28013/title.Juicy+J-Hot+Nigga+Freestyle|website=[[HipHopDX]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=July 21, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811012710/http://www.hiphopdx.com/index/singles/id.28013/title.Juicy+J-Hot+Nigga+Freestyle|archive-date=August 11, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[French Montana]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fleischer|first1=Adam|title=French Montana Shmoney Dances All Over Bobby Shmurda's 'Hot N\u2014a' Remix|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1889537/french-montana-bobby-shmurdas-hot-nigga-remix/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 5, 2014}}</ref> [[Lil' Kim]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Robertson|first1=Darryl|title=New Music: Lil Kim Jumps On Bobby Shmurda's 'Hot N**ga'|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/new-music-lil-kim-jumps-bobby-shmurdas-hot-nga|website=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 7, 2014}}</ref> [[Gunplay (rapper)|Gunplay]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rys|first1=Dan|title=Gunplay Throws Shots At 50 Cent On His \"Hot N***a\" Remix|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2014/08/gunplay-remix-bobby-shmurda-hot-nigga/|website=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> and [[T.I.]]<ref>{{cite web|title=New Music: T.I. \u2013 'Hot Ni**a (Remix)'|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/08/08/new-music-ti-hot-nigga-remix/|website=[[Rap-Up]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 8, 2014}}</ref> Following the song's viral success, Shmurda was signed to [[Epic Records]], and the song was officially released as his debut single under Epic.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Alexis|first1=Nadeska|title=Bobby Shmurda Signed A Record Deal\u2026 Break Out The Shmoney Dance|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1872163/bobby-shmurda-signed-a-record-deal-break-out-the-shmoney-dance/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 8, 2014|date=July 18, 2014}}</ref> The song topped the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop songs]] chart, and peaked at number 6 on the [[Billboard Hot 100]], eventually being certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]]. The music video received over 608 million views on YouTube as of December 2019.<ref name=\"billpake\">{{cite web|last1=Mendizabal|first1=Amaya|title=Iggy Azalea Closes In On Rap Chart Record With 'Fancy'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6214069/iggy-azalea-closes-in-on-rap-chart-record-with-fancy|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 9, 2014|date=August 7, 2014}}</ref> The song's official [[remix]]\u2014featuring [[guest vocals]] from [[Fabolous]], [[Chris Brown]], [[Jadakiss]], [[Rowdy Rebel]], [[Busta Rhymes]], and [[Yo Gotti]]\u2014was released on September 4, 2014.<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop1\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=New Music: Bobby Shmurda Feat. Fabolous, Jadakiss, Chris Brown, Busta Rhymes, Rowdy Rebel And Yo Gotti 'Hot Ni**a (Remix)'|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/new-music-bobby-shmurda-feat-fabolous-jadakiss-chris-brown-busta-rhymes-rowdy-rebel-and-yo-g|website=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=September 5, 2014|date=September 7, 2014}}</ref> A [[reggae]] remix of the song was also released in August 2014 that featured [[Junior Reid]], [[Mavado (singer)|Mavado]], [[Popcaan]], and Jah X.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Alexis|first1=Nadeska|title=Listen To Bobby Shmurda's Official Reggae Remix Of 'Hot N\u2014a'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1915924/bobby-shmurda-official-hot-n-a-remix/|website=MTV|accessdate=August 29, 2014|date=August 29, 2014}}</ref>\n\nShmurda's debut studio album with [[Epic Records]] was scheduled for release in 2016, being executively produced by [[Jahlil Beats]].<ref name=\"fader1\"/> It was postponed, however, due to his imprisonment.\n\nShmurda freestyled for rapper [[Meek Mill]] in February 2017 and claimed that he was still writing music while in prison.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spin.com/2017/02/bobby-shmurda-freestyle-prison/|title=Listen to Bobby Shmurda Deliver a Freestyle From Prison|date=February 28, 2017|work=Spin|access-date=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile incarcerated, he featured on fellow rapper [[6ix9ine]]'s single \"Stoopid\", released on October 5, 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/10/6ix9ine-bobby-shmurda-stoopid|title=Bobby Shmurda Guests on 6ix9ine's New Song \"Stoopid\"|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=October 6, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"6ix9ine\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/stoopid-feat-bobby-shmurda-single/1438155087|title=Stoopid \u2013 Single by 6ix9ine on Apple Music|publisher=Apple Inc|accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref> phoning in his verses over the prison telephone.\n\n==Legal issues==\nOn June 3, 2014, Shmurda was arrested and charged with felony criminal possession of a weapon. Police claim they saw him flashing the gun in an apartment and when they went to investigate, he tried to hide it in a couch. He was set free on $10,000 bail.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.contactmusic.com/story/rapper-bobby-shmurda-facing-gun-charge_4346237 | title=Bobby Shmurda \u2013 Rapper Bobby Shmurda Facing Gun Charge | date=August 29, 2014 | accessdate=August 29, 2014 | website=Contactmusic.com}}</ref> On December 17, 2014, police arrested Shmurda and 14 others, including his brother Javese and his fellow GS9 label-mate [[Rowdy Rebel]].<ref name=\"New York Post\"/> Police charged Shmurda with conspiracy to commit murder, [[reckless endangerment]], and drug and gun possession; charges against the others included murder, attempted murder, assault, and drug dealing.<ref name=WaPo />  Shmurda pleaded not guilty and was held on $2 million bail.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bobby-shmurda-jail-rikers-interview|title=Bobby Shmurda Speaks From Jail: 'People Are Trying to Take My Life Away for Being Blessed' (Exclusive)|website=Billboard|access-date=April 22, 2016|date=February 8, 2015}}</ref> Police said they had been investigating the gang for murder and shooting indiscriminately at crowds in public places long before Shmurda rose to fame. Police said Shmurda was \"the driving force\" in a gang also known as GS9 (standing for \"Grimey Shooters,\" \"Gun Squad\" or \"G Stone Crips.\"),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/music/bobby-shmurda-schmoney-dance-gs9/706897|title=A 20-Year-Old Kid From Brooklyn Just Owned Hip-Hop This Summer, Here's How|website=Elite Daily}}</ref> the name of his label, as they dealt crack and waged deadly battles with rival gangs for territory. He faced a maximum sentence of 8\u201325 years.<ref name=\"Yahoo News\">{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/ny-rapper-bobby-shmurda-faces-gun-drug-charges-065210216.html|title=NYC Rapper pleads not guilty to gun, drug charges|date=December 18, 2014|publisher=Yahoo News|agency=Associated Press|last1=Hays|first1=Tom|accessdate=December 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\nJames Essig, head of the [[NYPD]] unit that made the arrests, said Shmurda's songs and videos were \"almost like a real-life document of what they were doing on the street.\"<ref name=\"Yahoo News\"/> In his song \"[[Hot Nigga]]\", Shmurda rapped that \"I been selling crack since like the fifth grade\" because \"Jaja taught me\"; Shmurda also rapped about his crew's past and future murders.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hot Nigga Lyrics|url=https://genius.com/3451538/Bobby-shmurda-hot-nigga/And-tell-my-niggas-shmurda-teaming-ho-mitch-caught-a-body-bout-a-week-ago-week-ago|website=Genius Lyrics|accessdate=December 19, 2014}}</ref> Shmurda has asserted that the lyrics represent his real life in several interviews, though the [[Supreme Court of New Jersey]] recently ruled that lyrics cannot be read at trial as evidence unless they have a \"strong nexus\" to a specific crime.<ref name=WaPo>{{cite news|last1=Sullivan|first1=Gail|title=How rapper Bobby Shmurda, charged in murder, drug trafficking sting, became an alleged gangster|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/12/19/hip-hops-bobby-shmurda-charged-in-murder-drug-trafficking-sting/|accessdate=December 19, 2014|publisher=Washington Post|date=December 19, 2014}}</ref> During his jail time, Shmurda was involved in a suspected [[Bloods]] vs. [[Crips]] related fight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2015/05/16/bobby-shmurda-rapper-prison-gang-fight-guards/|title=Bobby Shmurda -- Knuckles Up for Crips vs. Bloods ... Jailhouse Edition|date=May 16, 2015|work=tmz.com|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nBetween late June and early July 2015, the rapper, along with his ex-girlfriend, were caught by officials having smuggled a knife into Rikers Island jail.<ref name=\"Vice\">{{cite news|last1=Hill|first1=John|title=BOBBY SHMURDA FACES MORE JAIL TIME AFTER SMUGGLING A KNIFE INTO JAIL \u2013 NOISEY|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/bobby-shmurda-knife-smuggle-charges-1|accessdate=June 23, 2015|publisher=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]}}</ref> The two were both charged with two counts of promoting contraband, in addition to one count of criminal possession of a weapon in the fourth degree, then that could result in an additional seven-year sentence. Shmurda appeared in the Bronx Supreme Court to face his charges of prison contraband plus 25 years for his previous charge in late 2014. He and his ex-girlfriend pleaded not guilty to the contraband charge, but Shmurda was still facing a maximum sentence of 25 years for the drug and gun charges.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bobby Shmurda & Girlfriend Plead Not Guilty to Her Smuggling Knife Into Prison: Report \u2013 Billboard|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6642034/bobby-shmurda-girlfriend-smuggling-knife-prison|date=July 24, 2015|accessdate=November 12, 2015|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bobby-shmurda-denied-bail-yet-again-trial-set-for-2016-news.18027.html | title=Bobby Shmurda Denied Bail Yet Again, Trial Set For 2016 | work=HotNewHipHop | date=October 5, 2015 | accessdate=January 30, 2016 | author=Schwartz, Danny}}</ref>\n\n=== Conviction ===\nOn September 2, 2016, as part of a [[plea deal]], Shmurda pleaded guilty to one count of third-degree conspiracy and one count of weapons possession, and was sentenced to seven years in prison. Under the deal, Shmurda cannot appeal the sentence, but will be given credit for two years served, leaving five years left on his sentence, followed by five years of probation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7503516/bobby-shmurda-accepts-plea-deal-serve-seven-years|title=Bobby Shmurda Accepts Plea Deal, Will Serve Seven Years|accessdate=September 20, 2016}}</ref> His lawyer [[Alex Spiro]] expects that with good behavior, Shmurda will only serve approximately three and a half years.<ref>{{cite news | accessdate=September 20, 2016 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/10/nyregion/rapper-bobby-shmurda-takes-7-year-plea-deal-in-gang-case.html | title=Rapper Bobby Shmurda Takes 7-Year Plea Deal in Gang Case | date=September 9, 2016 | last=Mckinley Jr, James C | first=. | newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> In early 2017, Shmurda was given a four-year sentence for sneaking a prison [[Shiv (weapon)|shiv]] into his cell. The sentence will run concurrently to his ongoing seven-year sentence, meaning he will not face any additional prison time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2017/04/07/bobby-shmurda-sentencing-shank-prison/|title=Bobby Shmurda Sentenced For Prison Shank|date=April 7, 2017|website=tmz.com}}</ref> Shmurda has a parole hearing scheduled for August 2020 and his conditional release date is scheduled to be December 11, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nysdoccslookup.doccs.ny.gov/GCA00P00/WIQ3/WINQ130|title=NYS Department of Corrections and Community Supervision|website=nysdoccslookup.doccs.ny.gov}}</ref>\n\n=== Incarceration ===\nShmurda was first imprisoned in [[Rikers Island]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.42243/title.bobby-shmurda-moves-prisons-after-someone-tries-to-stab-him|title=Bobby Shmurda Moves Prisons After Someone Tries To Stab Him|first=HipHopDX-|last=https://hiphopdx.com|date=February 3, 2017|website=HipHopDX}}</ref> He has been engaged in numerous incidents while incarcerated. In May 2015, Shmurda got in a brawl that included members from the [[Bloods]] and [[Crips]] street gangs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2015/05/bobby-shmurda-gang-related-jail-fight|title=Bobby Shmurda Was Reportedly Involved in a Gang-Related Jail Fight|website=Complex|language=en|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> In November 2016, Shmurda was involved in a brawl between several inmates that led to his losing phone privileges for an unnamed period of time and being sent to [[solitary confinement]] for a month.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bet.com/music/2017/04/03/bobby-shmurda-prison-job.html|title=Here's How Much Money Bobby Shmurda Is Reportedly Making With New Prison Job|work=BET.com|access-date=August 18, 2017}}</ref> In 2017 he was moved to [[Clinton Correctional Facility]] in upstate New York, to finish his sentence in [[protective custody]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://urbanislandz.com/2018/10/06/bobby-shmurda-looks-happy-prison-new-photo-family/|title=Bobby Shmurda Looks Happy In Prison In New Photo With Family|date=October 6, 2018|website=Urban Islandz}}</ref>\n\nImages of Shmurda while incarcerated surfaced online after three years served of a five-year plea deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bet.com/music/2017/08/10/bobby-shmurda-prison-photos.html|title=Photos Released of Bobby Shmurda as He Approaches 3 Years Behind Bars|work=BET.com|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, interviewer [[DJ Vlad]] conducted an interview with Shmurda over the phone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bobby Shmurda on Taking More Prison Time to Lessen Rowdy Rebel's Sentence (Part 1) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBQuJXDgEcg |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=djvlad |accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Mixtapes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with year released\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Shmoney Shmurda'' <small>(with GS9)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.datpiff.com/GS9-Shmoney-Shmurda-ShMixtape.629528.html|title=GS9 \u2013 Shmoney Shmurda (Shmixtape)|work=DatPiff|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: July 8, 2014\n*{{nowrap|Label: GS9}}\n* Format: Digital download\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Shmurdaville''\n|\n* Released: October 14, 2014\n*{{nowrap|Label: GS9}}, Shmurdaville\n* Format: Digital download\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:23em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.2em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=305|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605034714/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6228902/bobby%20shmurda/chart?f=305|archiv